The paper deals with the problem of Dirty Paper Coding (DPC) over a fading channel with partial transmitter side information (CSIT) and perfect receiver side information (CSIR). This problem falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of DPC in a multi-user transmission strategy, which could fall under the category of Multiple Access (cs.MM). The algorithms proposed in the paper involve iterative numerical methods, which could be related to the category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with the scaling behavior of the achievable rate in the high-SNR regime, which could be related to the category of Signal Processing (cs.SP).
